# Skill resource path rules (portable)

Applicable scenarios: writing or modifying`skills/**/SKILL.md`Match it`assets`/`router`document time.

## Mandatory requirements

- When referencing the template/resource path within a skill, the path relative to the skill directory must be used.
- It is forbidden to write warehouse root path references in skill descriptions (such as`skills/<name>/assets/...`).
- After the skill is installed into the user project, the path must be directly resolvable and not dependent on the current warehouse structure.

## Recommended writing method

-Same skill directory resources:`assets/<file>.md`- Router subdocument:`router/<file>.md`- Subdirectory resources:`assets/templates/<file>.md`## Prohibited writing

-`skills/spec-test-plan/assets/test_plan_template.md`
- `E:/dev/tools/sdlc-dev/skills/...`## Change self-test

- Check`SKILL.md`does it still exist in`skills/`Prefix resource reference.
- Confirm that newly added templates will not be split into language versions by default (no need to`_zh`/`_en`suffix) unless explicitly requested by the user.